      • refresh

        public void refresh()
        Closes and expands this Navigator's root node and repaints.

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

      • addModel

        public static void addModel​(AbstractModel model)
        Add a ModelNode (and possibly a plug-in node) for the given AbstractModel. This method also explores, expands and scrolls to the newly added node.

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel for which to add a ModelNode.

      • removeModel

        public static void removeModel​(AbstractModel model)
        Removes the given model from the Navigator's list of models as well as removing the ModelNode instance from the tree. If this was the last model in its plug-in node then the plug-in node will also be removed.

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel to remove

      • componentAdded

        public static void componentAdded​(AbstractModel model,
                                  AbstractComponent comp)
        Updates the tree in response to the given component being added to the given model. A ComponentNode will be created to represent the component and its parent CategoryNode will be updated to display the appropriate number of subnodes [n]. This method will also update any mini-navigator dialogs, so that adding child components will be reflected correctly.

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel containing the given component
        comp - the AbstractComponent that was added to the given model

      • componentRemoved

        public static void componentRemoved​(AbstractModel model,
                                    AbstractComponent comp)
        Updates the tree in response to the given component being removed from the given model. The component node will be found in the tree, and removed from its parent. This method will also update any mini-navigator dialogs, so that removing child components will be reflected correctly.

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel containing the given component
        comp - the AbstractComponent that was added to the given model

      • categoryChanged

        public static void categoryChanged​(AbstractModel model,
                                   Category category)
        Notifies the Navigator's nodes that the given category requires an update. This should be called when components are removed from the model.

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel whos category has changed.
        category - the Category whos contents have changed

      • modelChanged

        public static void modelChanged​(AbstractModel model)
        Updates the ModelNode for the given AbstractModel by calling nodeChanged on that node and repainting the Navigator.

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel that has changed

      • modelCategoriesChanged

        public static void modelCategoriesChanged​(AbstractModel model)
        UPdates the ModelNode for the given AbstractModel by rebuilding the children of the node and firing nodeStructureChanged. This method is required for situations where a model's category list has changed.

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel whos categories have changed.

      • expandComponentNodes

        public static void expandComponentNodes​(AbstractModel model,
                                        boolean collapseExisting,
                                        AbstractComponent... components)
        Expands the categorized ComponentNodes for the given components.

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel containing the given component
        collapseExisting - if true, the existing Navigator expansion will be collapsed prior to expanding and selecting the given components.

      • componentOrderChanged

        public static void componentOrderChanged​(AbstractModel model,
                                         Category category,
                                         int index)
        Notifies the NavigatorTreeModel that a component in the given model, with the given category, has changed order.

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel containing the component that changed order
        category - the Category of the component that changed order.
        index - the new index of the component that changed order; pass -1 if you do not want a node to be expanded after updating the component order.

      • childComponentOrderChanged

        NOTE: This method will perform this operation on the Swing event thread, ( via SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(java.lang.Runnable) if necessary. )

        Parameters:
        parent - the AbstractComponent containing the component that changed order
        category - the Category of the component that changed order.
        index - the new index of the component that changed order; pass -1 if you do not want a node to be expanded after updating the component order.
